Shareable APK Notes

Important
- Do not use APK files from `android/app/build/intermediates/...`.
- Use the shareable APK generated by `package-debug-apk.bat`.

Where to find the shareable APK
- Relative path (works in any project location): `dist/com.venjsx.mobile-debug.apk`
- Absolute path pattern: `<project-root>\\dist\\com.venjsx.mobile-debug.apk`

Build shareable APK
1. Open terminal in project root.
2. Run: `package-debug-apk.bat`

Install on connected phone (USB)
1. Run: `install-debug-apk.bat`
2. If package/signature conflict occurs, script retries with uninstall + install.

One-command flow
- `run-app.bat` builds, installs, and launches directly over USB.

Path reminder
- Repo can be anywhere: `C:\`, `Documents`, external drive, etc.
- Always rely on the relative output path: `dist/com.venjsx.mobile-debug.apk`.
